Upcoming Workshops & Groups

Check out our Workshops, Groups, and Trainings!

Enneagram Anytime workshops and groups are very interactive and heavily discussion based, because we want to help you personalize and truly integrate Enneagram knowledge. We limit the size of our workshops and groups to allow time for each attendee to get the individualized attention they need. Our workshops are not lengthy lectures paired with powerpoint presentations for you to sit back and digest. We want to hear how your type is showing up for you, and help you apply Enneagram wisdom to your everyday life. Check out the schedule below!

Whether you’re an individual who’s curious about the Enneagram for self-growth, or a Therapist, LCSW, Counselor, or Intern who wants to understand how the Enneagram could benefit your practice, you’re in the right place!

Before we get to the schedule, just a few notes:

  • All offerings are held virtually on Zoom

  • All times are in Pacific Time

  • Please note that there is a 24-hour cancellation policy for all workshops. Full refund is provided with notice 24 hours prior to the start of the workshop.

  • We offer CAMFT CEs with all of our workshops and groups for LMFTs, LCSWs, LPCCs, and/or LEPs who are interested. Details are noted on each event page. Please email elaineculverwell@gmail.com with any questions.

Click the image next to the event you’re interested in below to learn more and register!

The Enneagram Subtypes For Mental Health Professionals

  • Friday, May 19, 2023
  • 9:00 AM 4:00 PM
  • Google Calendar ICS

Join us for an interactive workshop on the Enneagram Instinctual Subtypes and how they can help you in your mental health practice. Learn more about how these body-based instinctual drives blend together with Enneagram type and deeply impact relationships. This workshop is available for 6.0 hours of CE credit. There is a registration fee of $150. (Early bird rate of $135 is available until May 5th.)
